\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No card games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. Oh no. Mother wouldn't pay - play cards anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 That was wicked was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - no, mother didn't like cards. She said they was the devil's playthings. Yes.
