\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 There was at the Grand Theatre. But of course that's all pulled down now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 You never went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Only when we got older. We - when we could - age of discretion. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you remember the first time you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh pantomimes, we used to go pantomime. Oh yes. Used to save the money up and go afternoon matinee - pantomimes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were they good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Used to have some good pantos then at the Grand Theatre. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have any pocket money, did your parents give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, not - a lot, because you see, it was - getting our clothes and food, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 You didn't have regular pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So much each week?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did anyone outside the house help your mother look after the house and family, did you have any relations who came in or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh - no, but we had a good neighbour next door, a Mrs Wilkins what u
sed to live next door, and she had a big family and mother did you see, so they used to help each other. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 If your mother was ill how did she manage, what happened, do you remember your mother being ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes, but - she had rheumatism bad, you
 see, and she used to have to lay in bed and - we used to - look after her and all like that, rub her and - the doctor used to come and - examine her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And between you you did the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How about friends, did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well - she - we was fr - friends with everybody, you know, mother was a good - mixer. And - like that but of course - the friends were kept - outside the front door. Mm. They never had a lot of friends inside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well, father didn't used to like the - what he used to say cackle and jaw. He says, 'cos you always - talk about somebody else where you should be talking about yourself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So you didn't have friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No, I don't think so, father and mother did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 People say that you made your own amusements in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well we had - we had these here mandolins and - ban}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2365796\charrsid355495 jo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 s and piano you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did mother and father play?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Like what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - in - in an office or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What were the next people up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - could say there is -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Would you think doctors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What about the real upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh, we always learnt to respect the upper class.. Oh yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Who were the upper class round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, the brewers and the doctors and - people like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did they live in big houses around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How were you taught to behave to them, did you have to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well just - respect them as they went by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have to call them sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes, when we spoke to them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Who was the most important person in your family life, who came to visit, was it the doctor or the vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh - no, didn't have a lot of - religion come here, not - vicars, unless my sister was ill and then the vicar would come down to see her.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Would you say that some of your friends were in different class levels from yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What sort?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, more a rougher kind. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What sort of people were the rough people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well I say weren't so much the children, it was the parents you see, who'd go out boozing and go home - three parts drunk of a night time.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How did they live, were they dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh - yes. Oh. Terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 But you used to play with their children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 I did. Yes. Then when I used to get inside - you've been playing with so and so. Well - she hadn't got anyone to play with mother. An
d I wasn't going to leaver her on her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How about the upper class children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh well they didn't - we didn't mix - too much with the upper class. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were they kept in their own circles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you think your mother and father saw themselves as belonging to the same class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Your mother didn't think she was different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Was it possible at that time to better yourself, to get to one class from another
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, no, father always work
ed - get his house paid off you see, and - keep a good home, clean home, and the family, and keep with - plenty of food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Would it have been possible for him to have got from his own middle class upwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh it would have done. Yes. But he - mother stopped him at that. Yes, she didn't want him to be - too clever.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well - a lot of his brothers - father's brothers - got money and made their way in Luton, and - they sort of - went - on the downward path. You see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 They didn't use their money properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 She didn't want that to happen to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So you think he could have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Oh he could have done, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you think it was possible to get from really working class upwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes, if you worked and saved. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And you could be accepted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you remember anybody being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh - the brewer and the doctors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 The brewer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. That was John William Green you know the - owner of a lot of pubs in Luton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And he was a gentleman was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. And she was a lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you remember seeing policemen around when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How did you think about the policemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were you frightened of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, we were - a - a bit because mother always - said, I'll tell a policeman of you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How do you think the police treated the people generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - with respect - them days. Oh yes. And we treated them with respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you ever remember times when your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh we did when - when the winter time was on you see, there was no straw work about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Was it seasonal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh - it's - it's - only seasonal. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Because people wore a different kind of hat in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Yes. Mm. Well you see there wasn't the felt hats then for the wintertime, like there is today. And - father wasn't in a big way so of course h
e couldn't afford the - blocking machines and - things like that what - what you had to have to do felt work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So what did he do in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - I don't know, he - he'd go out - gleaning or something like that you know in the fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 To get straw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And I suppose there was a little bit going on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 But you had to struggle hard to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you ever have any help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 From any kind of charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No. No. Father wouldn't have that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you remember your father being ill or off work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - he had a bad back once. He was took bad down his garden, and he - had to come down - Old Bedford Road - on two sticks. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you remember anybody around here who was disapproved of by everybody, so much so that they tried to get rid of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well I don't think it was that sort of - hateful snobbishness years ago - like there would be today. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Occasionally they used to do things like making life so difficult for somebody that they had to leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Yes. Well if they were really dirty, you know - and they - moved to one of these houses, they would have a complaint from the sanitary people, and they would have to either - pull th
eir socks up and - and clean the houses up - and their children, you see, or - or - get out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did the neighbours complain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well I don't know, I don't remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Would they do anything about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. Not like they would today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Can you tell me whereabouts in the house the hats were made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh all over the house. Oh - in bedrooms and downstairs, anywhere where we could sit, got a chair - and could sit down. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Where were the materials kept for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - bunged anywhere. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have to clear the table in order to get a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes, father wouldn't let us have our work on the table at mealtimes. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 But you'd do it on the table and then clear it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes, that's right, yes. Yes, that's right, for a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How did mother divide her duty between doing the hats and doing the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well - had to work it in, you know. Yes. It's surprising what - when you've got to do it how you - you know, put on with one get - get it done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did she do the housework first in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well - we used to go up and - and - do the vegetables, and - fetch the meat or anything like that and - and see the beds are made and all the necessary things to come downstairs and - the same as wash days and all like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And then the hat work would be fitted in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
When other people came from outside to do work on the hats in busy times did they come to the house or did father take the work out to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Mm. Well it'
s all according. If father had got the time he would take 'em but if not one of us would take them. In a sheet or a - a box. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And then people would do it in their houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes, and then bring 'em back to us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How were the hats sold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 We used to take 'em down in - to a big - hat factory down the street you see. And - they would sell them for us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you put the prices on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh they - we - we took the sample in, and you see, get a price for them, then they'd order from them - that sample you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So your father would fix the price?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And those people would buy from him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Well buy through the firm, and the orders would be sent up to our house you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 I should think there was hardly room to move was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well we - we got round you know. Yes. Surprising really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 You had to be very tidy though didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh we was always very tidy. Yes, never had to - you know, lay any things about like I do now. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 This girl that you adopted, the girl who came into the family who's mother wasn't very nice to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh - Maude Freeman. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What age did she come to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 She was - about sixteen when she come. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did she come as one of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well she come and - helped mother you see, and then she worked in the family you know, and she joined the family - without us really knowing it you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 She was never made any different to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 She was one of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So mother didn't pay her wages or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 She just looked after her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And she was expected to help as much as the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Wet more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - you know - she'd - turn her sleeves up if there was anything to be done she'd do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Sixteen was quite grown up in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did she ever go back to see her people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well she used to see them about the town. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 But she took on your family as her family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. And my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you know what happened to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
She got married. Yes. And - she lived down Park Street, and - she married quite a nice fellow. Yes. And had a family, you know. And all that, but she always - mum and dad, you know, our family, was always mum and dad to her. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did the man do that she married, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well I don't know you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 But he was a nice chap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Then your own brothers and sisters, can you remember what they did later in life? Alfred for instance, he was first wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 He was in the army for about - you know, 'til he was about fifteen - sixteen, out in Egypt. Yes. He come home and he'd just - s
tarted learning to drive a car for John William Green the brewer, and - then when he come back, he'd been out in Egypt in all that heat - some other man what hadn't been in the army, and that - you know, crept and took his job, so when Alf come back he ha
d to go out into the garden, do the garden.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 That was hard luck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 It was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did he do gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No, he - he drove the car you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What happened after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, he had pneumonia, my brother had pneumonia, you see, b
ecause being out in the heat all the while you see, then come over and out in the bitter cold in the wintertime, you see, of course he - yes. Well he - as soon as he could see a better job he soon got out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did he do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - went - drive - motor driving for a - engineering factory, up - oh - Brown and Green's, iron founders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And that's what he did the rest of his working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Who was the next one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Alf - well, me. Yes. I was a - straw hat made you know and - general dogs - body.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 There's nobody after me. I was the youngest one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 We started at the bottom then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Tell me about some of the others then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 There was Arthur, my - oldest brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
In - in the straw hat - worked for - a shop in - Bute Street, selling the plait to make the hats with. Yes. Used to take it out for this - shop you know. And - he - if he had bales of it to take out he got a horse and cart he could - r
un the - bale up on the cart and take that you see. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 It was ordinary straw was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. You know - you know straw plait don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well I've never been it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Haven't you? Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Is it long straw plaited up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Mm. My mother could - plait the straw. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How wide would a plait be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well it's all according. Some used to be inch, inch and a half and two inches. We had plait - two and a half inches sometimes you know, done on a box machine. Our machines were small
 ones for the dressed hensia and they used to be a little - for small - not - plaited plaits, but machine made plaits, you see, like crinny or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Crinney?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Crinley, yes. In - in - you know those floppy hats like they wear at Ascot, we used to make them. Mm. Mm. Fine - straw.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did he go on doing that for the rest of his working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No, he - he still kept - motor - in the motor line. We've never been one to change our jobs much. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Who else was there, we've done you and we've done Alfred and Arthur?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And who else was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 There was George - George, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did George do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 He was a driver for Brown - for Greens up at the Larches, he was the head chauffer up there you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 That was a good job was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Well - for them sort of people, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did he get treated well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes, they treated him all right but - he didn't care, you know, he just went on his own sweet way. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did he do that all his working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
No - oh he - he always - drove - Mr Green, and Mrs Green. Matter of fact they wouldn't let anyone else drive 'em, only - my brother then. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 That was George?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 George, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 You call him Ben?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes. Always called him Ben.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And then there was Sid wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did Sid do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - he worked - for - Brightman the butcher. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 As a butcher boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. You know, delivering meat. And then - one day - Mr Brightman said to him, Si
d, 'cos he was - oh he was a crafty little wretch you know, jump up on anything and all like that, well he jumped this time - you know, that's the final jump he done. He was always scrambling to get up on horses. And - he - so Mr Brightman said to him - S
i
d, will you fetch my horse off the park on Sunday and bring it home? 'Cos - my - he dare do anything, Sid dare, you know, catch a horse and - yes, throw a bit of rope over its head you know and make a halter of it you know and just walk side of it. Oh yes
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well you see, he went up - the p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2365796\charrsid355495 ark and there'd been a - footbal}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 ling up there Saturday and - the goalposts - you know, where the - goal - goaling posts go in, like that, well - the top of that hadn't been put back. This horse
 - put its foot in it, and throwed my brother you see and broke his leg. Mm. And he was taken up the - Bute Hospital, but of course they never set - set it right you see. It was one Sunday when - my - brother - broke his leg, and of course that was before
 
any motor ambulances and that about you see and - of course - father would be able to send for the doctor and he come and - he said, oh he said I can't do anything here, he says, he put the splint up each side of his leg, and - then they - took him to the
 
- Bute hospital. But you see - it happened to be of the Sunday night, although we was private patients, it didn't make no difference, you see, this doctor - Smithson, he didn't like to be called out on a Sunday so of course, he hurried it, and instead of 
the - foot - being set like that, you see, straight, he set it on the cross. And my brother was a cripple right the way - it started - his leg all going. Mm. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did he do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well he - it - he got about as much as he could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did he have a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, he - yes, he - oh he'd find a job, you know, somewhere or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Just casual jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How sad, because he sounded a bright lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 He did. And matter of fact, if - it hadn't have been for the accident father 
would have had him trained as a jockey. 'Cos that's what he wanted to be. Yes. Oh he wanted to - he loved horses. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And he was small was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. And he hadn't got a care in the world you know. He wouldn't be a - a - a cruel to - any animal, but he loved horses. Yes. Mm. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Who else was there, any more boys? We've got Alfred Arthur, George and Sid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh there's Frankie was in straw work. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 All his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Doing what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - he worked for - a man, you know, he went out to work and worked for this here man, in - Reginald Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Was that plaiting the straw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
No, well - blocking the hats. You see, when the hats was machined - he'd stiffen them and then block them in the big blocking machine, to make the shape of 'em. Hat blocker he was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Is that all the boys now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Alfred, Arthur, George, Sid and Frank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 We know what happened to Maude now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Mm. She got married. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And we know what happened to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 You went on in the straw work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 When did you stop working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well I stopped working - when it stopped me working, when I had this here illness. Mm. I kept on - working the same as if - I was working - in the house here
 - the day before I went for a half a day outing, and I had this stroke. Yes, worked right up 'til the last. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you go out to work once the straw hat thing was finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Went to work at George Kents in - Miscot Road, the engineering place. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did you do there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - we had to do anything you see. Inspect - fuse - fuses and - scr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2365796\charrsid355495 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 ws and all things like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes, I didn't mind it at all. I preferred it to straw work. Yes, you got - we got more money for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 I should think you'd had your basin full of straw work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Oh I did, yes. 'Cos it was a harassing trade. Oh yes. When there - where there's any work but you've got to - sit and work, wouldn't matter what it was. That was it
, of course - Sundays - mm - they wouldn't - father wouldn't let you - and mother wouldn't let you touch a - a - a needle on Saturday - Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No matter how much work there was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Then of course you'd get your blank patches I expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2365796\charrsid355495 yes. Yes, too many blank patche}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 s there was. Yes. Mmm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Any more girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - a - a sister what died, Lil. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How old was she when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 She was about thirty-five. But she'd been ill for years and years and years, with bronchial asthma.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did she ever have a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No, she always done a little straw work at home for father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did she get married,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No, there's nobody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No other sisters?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So that's three girls and five boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Five boys, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Where did your family have the - meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well we used to - when we'd finished straw work, we'd always clear the table and then put the table cloth on and set the table and have our meals in the living room. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you ever eat in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well Christmastime you know in the front room. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What sort of cooker did your mother use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 An ordinary gas cooker. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 About what time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes, a
lways mother used to get up early of a morning and make a cup of tea and come down and start frying the breakfast, you know eggs and bacon and fried bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And did you all have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh - well, you know, as we come down. Yes, relay
s. Mother used to call a lot of us up the stairs, your breakfast is ready, come on, I can't keep it hot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And you'd all come down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 About what time would that be, eight o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 About - about half past eight. 'Cos we always liked our bed. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did you have to drink at breakfast, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Tea. Father and mother had coffee. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 The rest of you had tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. We could have had coffee if we'd have liked, but I didn't like coffee then. No, but I like it now. No. I didn't like it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have anything different on Sundays for instance for breakfast, did you have a bigger breakfast on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - no, I don't think so, 'cos - mother always see as we had a good meal before we went out of the mornings. Always
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 She set store by it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What sort of meal did you have in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - a proper cooked dinner. Vegetables, two vegetables and - meat and pudding, or - a roast with Yorkshire and all like 
that, yes. Oh always had a - a proper - dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How many times a week would you have had meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh every day. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well that used to be - cheese, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2365796\charrsid355495 done in front of the fire in a D}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 utch oven. You know, so it all runs down. Yes. Toasted cheese, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did you have to drink then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Hot cocoa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did your mother and father have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Beer. Always used to have a glass of beer - with their supper, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did father go and fetch it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Father used to go and fetch it in the jug. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 That was every evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did mother make her own bread at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Or jams or pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh she always made pickles. Oh yes. We used to have a cupboard up there a
nd that used to be packed with pickles. Cabbage, onions - and - walnuts. And - tomato chutney and all things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 I don't know how she found time to make them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well you - we all had to stir the pots you know if mother was busy. Come on, stir this pot. Some of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How about wine or home brewed beer, did they ever do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you ever have any tinned vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No. Always fresh from the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 You had your own vegetables and fruit in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did they have any livestock, hens, pigs, goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh we had 'em all round the garden. Yes. Down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you ever have any extra meat, did anybody give you a chicken or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no - father used to - more like give - the eggs and chickens away to anyone round the neighbourhood who was ill. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 He was generous was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh - father was. And so was mother. Yes. After mother died - a lot of people, used t
o stop me and they said, you know, about mother, they said, oh, they says, we shouldn't have had a dinner on Sundays if it hadn't been for your poor mother. Yes, oh - she - she wouldn't let anyone know that you was going to get it, but she'd get a bit of 
meat you know, and - do it up in a parcel and put it in a basket and - go round and see Mrs Odle or - someone like that you see and take 'em a little something. So they had a dinner on Sunday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 That was very kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you ever remember mother having less food so that you could have more when there wasn't enough to go round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well we had a - enough, I don't know how it was bu we always had plenty on the table. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did father have bigger helpings than anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Could you have second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 As much as you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. Well not - you know, too much of it, 'cos father'd say, what's this - talking machine
 - going? No, father used to like us to sit quietly. And so to digest our food. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Could you leave things you didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - I - say - you know we were handed our plates up, mother I don't want any you know, pudding, yes. All right then. 
You leave it and - you can have - something else for your supper then, you know. OH yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So you weren't forced to eat up what you didn't want?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were you expected to have good table manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you always sit in the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well we - always liked to, father used to sit at the head, and I used to sit next to father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were you his favourite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well I - I was the youngest one you see and you always reckon to make a little bit of favourite don't you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were you fond of your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - I liked father and mother, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Equally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes, both - do you know, I never knew my mother or father ever to smack us, you know, or knock us about. Oh no. Mother use
d to say, if you knock one devil out you knock two in. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How about bringing a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Or a toy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How were you served, did it go round the table or oldest to youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Father, mother used 
to sit there and father used to sit there. Father used to do the carving of the meat, the joint, and mother used to have the two vegetables dishes there and there, and - she would put the vegetables on our plates and then - get the meat off the dish what 
father had cut, you see, and - there used to be the gravy tureen and she put the gravy on the - oh and the Yorkshire, oh yes. Never had like - mother used to make a lovely Yorkshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 It's not easy is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - it's - all right when you've done it once or twice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have the sort that rose up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Or flat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. Rise - rising up ones, yes. And the meat - standing on the - tray and dripping the fat in - into the meat. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So it had all the juices out of the meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Maud ate with you didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 She wasn't treated any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you ever remember people calling your mother and father madam or sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No, always say Mr and Mrs Rosson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were they respectful to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes, oh yes. Oh 'course mother never quarrelled with anybody. Nor would father. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And they were respected by the people around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did people come to them when they were in trouble at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well we were never in trouble, you know, not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 I mean other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh they would have come, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What sort of people would the shopkeepers have gone around with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Mother used to deal - at Barford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6628774\charrsid355495 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 s, that was a general grocer at the corner of North Street there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were you friends with the Barford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6628774\charrsid355495 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 s out of the shop at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No, mother'd always speak to them and they'd always speak to mother you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Who would have been the close friends of the Barford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6628774\charrsid355495 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 s, would people in trade stick together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh trades, trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6628774\charrsid355495 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 people really used to be together more. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How about vicars and parsons and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - you see, mother was always Church of England, you see, and - she - and we always went to c
hurch, you see, so of course - if the parson - come round to see us he was always made welcome. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you ever go to the vicarage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Who would be friends of the parson?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - all of us children would be. And - as we went t
o church, you know, Sundays, the - their children would be sitting in the - seats you know and we'd then sit beside of them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you remember who teachers would associate with, who would they be friends with? Did they stick to themselves or were t
hey friends with other people outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - they used to be friendly, I don't know how it was in Luton but we always was friends - with each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 There wasn't much division between people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What was the difference between the people that went to church and those who went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well - the church people were more - straight forward. But with the chapel people they was a little bit narrow, and they didn't like it because father used to go and fetch his beer - in a jug. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did they think that was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Yes. So - father said to 'em - one day to a man, he said - you'll go to hell for drinking that beer. So said father, I shan't go to heaven if I don't. Father had always got an answer for them. He said, when 
I pay for it, he said, I shan't - ask you or anybody else what I'm going to drink. Oh yes. They - they're very narrow minded. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did your mother and father have the same ideas about the other classes or was your mother stricter about you not mixing with poor children?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
No. No. There was no snobbery about father and mother. But she didn't like us - mixed in with dirty children, you know, heads dirty or anything like that. Oh a lot of that about. Yes, there did, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 I suppose you had to be careful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you ever pick up anything at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh I did. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did they do for it in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh, they used to - mother always used to - wash hour hair every Saturday night, you know, before she had the b
ath in front of the fire, and bath us all and got us ready for Sunday, that's been a real good ritual you know, have all the clothes round the fire airing off. And then mother would get the hot water and the bath out and put it in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6628774\charrsid355495  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 front of the fire and - we all get in - in it you know different times and - get the warm towels and get into bed and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have your hair washed at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 We always had our hair washed before we got into the bath. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did she put anything special on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Rankin's ointment. For - nits and lice. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And you always had that on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Yes. Mm. You know, she could plait - plait our hair all right round and make two crowns of it and all like that - and of course mum was always wonderfully straight ha
ir, yes, wonderfully straight. Whereas my sister had got a bit of a kink in hers, she could put her hand like that you see and she could make - make a wave, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Which sister was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Maud. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did your parents ever give you any teaching at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no. They - they'd - got enough to do to - try and get our living. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 When you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Fourteen. Oh - thirteen. Thirteen I went - 'cos mother was glad enough to get - get us out the house you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Didn't you go to a little school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No, went to the - Old Bedford Road Board School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 About thirteen I think. As soon as they'd take us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Didn't you go to any school before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No. Only Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 You stayed at home until you were thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So could you read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes, O could read all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How did you learn to read then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - you know - mother or my siste
rs or brothers, you know, would - be reading. And read the paper to us and tell us all what was in the paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 So didn't you go to any school at all until you were thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did any of you in the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 You stayed at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 When did you leave school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 When I was about fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you only have one year at school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no, I had about - five years at school. About - thirteen. You see, I mentioned I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Can you remember how did you go to school, did you walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh it - it was only just along the road and down by Bedford Road School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 It wasn't far then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you all go together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No, we all went - you know, as we got ourselves ready, or mother g
ot us ready, and - let's look at your hands, have you got your hands clean, and all like that, have you washed? Yes mother. Right-o. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you go all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. You know, come home at dinnertime, have our dinner, and go back after school - after dinner again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Was it a mixed school or just girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Girls and boys, but they was in separate classes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Separate playgrounds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. No. Yes, playgrounds, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you like school when you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well I liked it all
 right, but of course I - I - couldn't sit down and study all - like that - I was a bit of a dunce and so of course I wasn't very popular with teachers, and all like that, but if they'd give me anything to do - that's more than my life was worth if I had 
t
o go home and tell - tell her I ain't done it. Yes, she'd say don't you come home here tomorrow and tell 'em - tell me your teacher's hit you because I shan't go up the school. You'll fight your own battles. Yes. She wouldn't - you know, encourage us to -
 cheek the teachers or anything like that. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And that applied to all of you did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes, yes. Now behave yourselves. She'd say. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How about the teachers, did you have more than one teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, we - went up in classes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Can you remember the teachers making any great thing about manners or punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes, they always drummed that into us you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 The way you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have to be polite to the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Yes. You see, we was always polite to our own parents so that was nothing change to us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 It came naturally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How did they punish children at your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 A cane. Always got hold your hand out. Get a - and you had to go to the governess for that. Oh I can see her now. That cane. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 That was the head teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 You called her the governess?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Was she fierce?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 She - well she'd look - ever so black at you. You know, the tears was coming up - in me face.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What sort of thing would you get the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well for talking. 'Cos I was always a talker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did they cane children a lot, did you have to do very much to get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well it was - a - childish naughtiness really, I used to get the cane for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did somebody get the cane every day more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Oh no, I don't think so. No, they weren't all that cruel, not - well-not at Old Bedford Road School. They make you mind and you've got to - behave yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were boys punished the same as the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No - the boys were punished more than we were. Yes, because they played up more - with the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have some tough children in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - not - rough - tough people. We was all - about the same - standard, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did the teachers have favourites can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Sometimes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What sort of child would be a favourite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, the one that was always the top of the class. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 That's why you weren't favourite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. But I was always at the top of the class for painting. Yes, always. Yes, I could - and painting and drawing. Yes. Map drawing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you ever think that you'd have done better if you'd have had more education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well I don't know about more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Would you have liked to have gone on and done a bit more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, not - in the position we were then, 'cos it was all straw work you see, getting your living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 That was most important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes it was then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Do you ever wish you could have done more painting and drawing for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No, I didn't - don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Go on to art school or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Didn't it ever occur to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well, I - my teacher use
d to say - to mother when she used to come up open days you know - you've got a talented daughter there. That was me. And mother used to say - talented? Yes, she'd say, she's very talented, especially with her paint box and - her pens and things. And mine
 always used to be stuck up on the board. All my drawing, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did mother put them up at home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
No. What you bought - what rubbish you brought home now? Mum I've done and got first prize for this at school. Oh well - you'll be teacher's pet then tomorrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 But she didn't think it was very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 When the war broke out the straw work stopped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And you went up to the engineering works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Yes. The - on munitions you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 I went and asked for it. Oh yes. Oh I'd go in anywhere and ask for a job. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What sort of hours did you work, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Let's see, it was - half past - half past seven - 'til - sometime in the evening, you know, 
about - it's all according to how old we were, you see, they wouldn't let you work, not too long them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 When you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 That was quite early to start in the morning wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Some Saturdays. It's all according what work they'd got you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Never on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have a half day holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 When - they used to have the school holidays, you know, for - bonfire - nights we'd - perhaps have a - a
 - afternoon out, from school, yes. To go round and get some twigs and all like that to make a bonfire with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 When you were working at the engineering works did you have a fortnights holiday or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 A week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Was that paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you give any of your money that you earned to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh I had to pay me board. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Was there a lot of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have to give her quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you have much left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - if we earnt - twenty-five - shillings - we'd give - give mother a pound you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 And have five shillings yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes. You - I'd to save - save some you know, have a post office book and go down - pay it in the post office. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 What did you spend your money on, what was left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well I never went out and about much you know, 'cos we'd got a good home and - plenty of food there you see so - we was a family - you know, all in one. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you like the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh I got on with everybody. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were there lots of girls there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh yes. Just started out to work like myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 How did the employer treat you, was there a Mr Kent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well there was, but you see, he was - well up you see, Mr George Kent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you ever see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well he used to come through the factories, you know, walk through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did he talk to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Well - if he saw any of us - you know, waiting for work and all like that he'd say - you don't look very busy, you 
know, say, no sir, waiting for some work to come along. Oh, I'll see it comes along - soon, like that you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Were they nice to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Oh - oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 They treated you well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868611 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 Did you like the work you were doing or did you find it monotonous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5120987 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14769093\charrsid355495 
Well I - I didn't mind work at all. I liked - I liked being at work, you know, and being busy. I'd always been a - busy person you know, and - yes.
